quran[5]{c,v,t}:
  13,14,"Calling upon Him ňĻaloneňļ is the truth. But those ňĻidolsňļ the pagans invoke besides Him ňĻcanňļ never respond to them in any way. ňĻIt isňļ just like someone who stretches out their hands to water, ňĻasking itňļ to reach their mouths, but it can never do so. The calls of the disbelievers are only in vain"
  13,15,"To Allah ňĻaloneňļ bow down ňĻin submissionňļ¬†all those in the heavens and the earth‚ÄĒwillingly or unwillingly‚ÄĒas do their shadows, morning and evening"
  13,16,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúWho is the Lord of the heavens and the earth?‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúAllah!‚ÄĚ Ask ňĻthemňļ, ‚ÄúWhy ňĻthenňļ have you taken besides Him lords who cannot even benefit or protect themselves?‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúCan the blind and the sighted be equal? Or can darkness and light be equal?‚ÄĚ¬†Or have they associated with Allah partners who ňĻsupposedlyňļ produced a creation like His, leaving them confused between the two creations? Say, ‚ÄúAllah is the Creator of all things, and He is the One, the Supreme.‚ÄĚ"
  13,17,"He sends down rain from the sky, causing the valleys to flow, each according to its capacity. The currents then carry along rising foam, similar to the slag produced from metal that people melt in the fire for ornaments or tools. This is how Allah compares truth to falsehood. The ňĻworthlessňļ residue is then cast away, but what benefits people remains on the earth. This is how Allah sets forth parables"
  13,18,"Those who respond to ňĻthe call ofňļ their Lord will have the finest reward. As for those who do not respond to Him, even if they were to possess everything in the world twice over, they would certainly offer it to ransom themselves. They will face strict judgment, and Hell will be their home. What an evil place to rest"